WEBVTT

00:02.794 --> 00:04.003
♪ TIMMY IS AN AVERAGE KID ♪

00:04.086 --> 00:07.799
♪ THAT NO ONE UNDERSTANDS ♪

00:07.882 --> 00:10.510
{\an1}♪ MOM AND DAD AND VICKY
ALWAYS GIVING HIM COMMANDS ♪

00:10.593 --> 00:12.595
BED, TWERP!

00:12.679 --> 00:13.888
{\an1}♪ THE DOOM AND GLOOM
UP IN HIS ROOM ♪

00:13.972 --> 00:16.599
♪ IS BROKEN INSTANTLY ♪

00:16.683 --> 00:19.936
♪ BY HIS MAGIC LITTLE FISH
WHO GRANT HIS EVERY WISH ♪

00:20.019 --> 00:20.854
♪ BECAUSE IN REALITY ♪

00:20.937 --> 00:23.773
♪ THEY ARE HIS ODDPARENTS ♪

00:23.857 --> 00:24.983
♪ FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:25.066 --> 00:25.942
WANDS AND WINGS!

00:26.025 --> 00:26.860
FLOATY, CROWNY THINGS!

00:26.943 --> 00:29.779
{\an1}♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:29.863 --> 00:32.448
{\an1}♪ REALLY MOD, PEA POD,
BUFF BOD, HOT ROD ♪

00:32.531 --> 00:33.450
♪ OBTUSE,
RUBBER GOOSE ♪

00:33.533 --> 00:34.242
♪ GREEN MOOSE,
GUAVA JUICE ♪

00:34.325 --> 00:35.076
♪ GIANT SNAKE,
BIRTHDAY CAKE ♪

00:35.160 --> 00:37.996
♪ LARGE FRIES,
CHOCOLATE SHAKE! ♪

00:38.079 --> 00:40.331
{\an1}♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:40.415 --> 00:42.917
{\an1}♪ IT FLIPS YOUR LID
WHEN YOU ARE THE KID ♪

00:43.001 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}♪ WITH FAIRLY ODDPARENTS! ♪

00:44.794 --> 00:45.670
{\an8}Vicky: YEAH, RIGHT.

00:48.965 --> 00:50.884
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY

00:50.967 --> 00:53.136
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION

00:58.308 --> 01:00.810
Wanda: COSMO, WHERE ARE YOU?

01:00.894 --> 01:03.396
TIMMY, HAVE YOU SEEN COSMO?

01:03.480 --> 01:04.647
HAVEN'T SEEN HIM,

01:04.730 --> 01:05.815
BUT HAVE YOU SEEN THIS?

01:05.899 --> 01:06.983
IT'S FLIPSIE,
THE FLIPPING DOG.

01:07.066 --> 01:10.153
IT'S THE PINNACLE
OF FLIPPING TECHNOLOGY.

01:10.236 --> 01:10.987
I'VE GOT TO HAVE IT!

01:11.070 --> 01:13.448
TIMMY, I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS.

01:13.531 --> 01:14.824
I HAVE TO FIND COSMO.

01:14.908 --> 01:16.951
IT'S HIS 1,000-YEAR
CHECK-UP TODAY,

01:17.035 --> 01:20.914
AND HE'S AFRAID
OF THE D-O-C-T-O-R.

01:20.997 --> 01:24.709
{\an1}HA HA! A LAMP--
THE PERFECT DISGUISE.

01:24.793 --> 01:25.710
WELL, SINCE
I CAN'T FIND COSMO,

01:25.794 --> 01:29.005
I MIGHT AS WELL POOF UP
SOME JUICY, FATTENING,

01:29.088 --> 01:31.007
ARTERY-CLOGGING
BACON STRIPS

01:31.090 --> 01:33.843
AND SHARE THESE
SUCCULENT STRIPS OF PORK

01:33.927 --> 01:37.639
{\an5}WITH MY SUCCULENT
EX-BOYFRIEND
JUANDISSIMO.

01:37.722 --> 01:39.891
WANDA, CAN IT BE TRUE?

01:39.974 --> 01:40.767
IT IS FANTASY COME TO LIFE.

01:40.850 --> 01:43.686
YOU WITHOUT COSMO,
FEEDING ME CARNE.

01:43.770 --> 01:46.523
SOMEBODY PINCH ME--

01:46.606 --> 01:48.525
PREFERABLY YOU.

01:48.608 --> 01:52.862
{\an1}HEY! GET YOUR SUCCULENT HANDS
OFF MY BACON!

01:52.946 --> 01:55.156
{\an1}I HATE IT WHEN YOU
USE ME AS BAIT,

01:55.240 --> 01:58.326
AND YET I LOVE IT.

01:58.409 --> 01:58.910
HERE, BOY.

01:58.993 --> 01:59.536
GET THE BACON.
GET IT.

01:59.619 --> 02:04.040
GET THE BACON!

02:04.123 --> 02:07.627
OH, NO! TIMMY, HELP!
I'M TRAPPED!

02:07.710 --> 02:10.588
I MEAN, LOOK AT THIS THING.
IT'S FOOLPROOF.

02:10.672 --> 02:12.298
I'LL NEVER GET OUT OF HERE.

02:12.382 --> 02:13.967
WAIT. WANDA, NO.

02:14.050 --> 02:16.427
{\an1}YOU CAN'T TAKE COSMO.
WHAT IF I NEED SOMETHING,

02:16.511 --> 02:18.054
LIKE FLIPSIE?

02:18.137 --> 02:19.347
[GROANS]

02:21.140 --> 02:21.641
WHAT'S THAT?

02:21.724 --> 02:23.184
A MAGIC COPY MACHINE.

02:23.268 --> 02:26.521
{\an1}IF YOU NEED SOMETHING,
JUST PUT THE PICTURE HERE,

02:26.604 --> 02:28.231
PRESS THE "WISH" BUTTON,

02:28.314 --> 02:29.482
AND...

02:31.526 --> 02:32.235
OH, MY GOSH!

02:32.318 --> 02:34.863
{\an1}IT'S FLIPSIE,
MY DREAM COME TRUE!

02:34.946 --> 02:36.531
{\an4}BYE, COSMO.
HAVE A GREAT TIME
AT THE DOCTOR'S.

02:36.614 --> 02:38.783
{\an1}WHAT? DOCTOR? I THOUGHT
SHE WAS SPELLING "PLUMBER."

02:38.867 --> 02:40.410
IT'S WORSE THAN I THOUGHT!

02:40.493 --> 02:43.621
NOOO!

02:43.705 --> 02:46.457
COME ON. FLIP.

02:46.541 --> 02:48.585
FLIP. FLIP, ALREADY!

02:48.668 --> 02:49.961
THIS STINKS.

02:50.044 --> 02:51.129
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO NOW?

02:51.212 --> 02:53.548
ALL I HAVE IS
THIS MAGIC COPY MACHINE

02:53.631 --> 02:56.426
AND A CATALOG OF COOL TOYS
I COULD COPY AND MAKE REAL.

03:04.100 --> 03:07.228
{\an1}THIS MAGIC COPY MACHINE
COULD DO ANYTHING.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.355
EXCEPT MAKE YOU FLIP.

03:11.941 --> 03:12.483
WHY WON'T YOU FLIP?

03:14.944 --> 03:17.739
[MACHINE BEEPING]

03:17.822 --> 03:21.200
[LAUGHING]

03:21.284 --> 03:22.952
HOW'S MY COSMO,
DR. STUDWELL?

03:23.036 --> 03:28.041
CALL ME DR. RIP STUDWELL.

03:28.124 --> 03:29.083
{\an1}AND I'M AFRAID
I HAVE SOME BAD NEWS.

03:29.167 --> 03:31.461
WHAT IS IT,
DR. RIP STUDWELL?

03:31.544 --> 03:35.965
{\an4}AFTER A SERIES
OF INCREDIBLY PAINFUL
AND HUMILIATING TESTS,

03:36.049 --> 03:40.553
WE BELIEVE COSMO MAY BE...

03:40.637 --> 03:41.638
STUPID.

03:41.721 --> 03:45.058
NO!

03:45.141 --> 03:46.976
OH, WAIT. I KNEW THAT.

03:47.060 --> 03:48.311
HOW STUPID IS HE?

03:48.394 --> 03:50.355
I'LL LET OUR SPECIALIST
CLARIFY.

03:50.438 --> 03:54.442
PLEASE PUT YOUR HANDS TOGETHER
FOR THE APRIL FOOL.

03:54.525 --> 03:58.196
{\an5}COSMO IS SO STUPID,
IF HIS BRAINS
WERE DYNAMITE,

03:58.279 --> 04:00.615
HE WOULDN'T HAVE ENOUGH
TO BLOW HIS NOSE.

04:00.698 --> 04:02.116
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT?

04:02.200 --> 04:02.992
GOOD NIGHT, EVERYBODY!

04:03.076 --> 04:04.494
NO! I'M NOT STUPID!

04:04.577 --> 04:07.664
{\an5}AND I CAN PROVE IT
IF YOU'LL LET ME
OUT OF HERE.

04:07.747 --> 04:09.290
BUT COME ON!

04:09.374 --> 04:12.919
EVEN HOUDINI COULDN'T
ESCAPE THIS.

04:13.002 --> 04:15.505
IT'S WORSE THAN I...

04:15.588 --> 04:16.047
DR. RIP STUDWELL...

04:16.130 --> 04:18.423
COULD HAVE THOUGHT.

04:25.098 --> 04:27.308
LET'S SEE...
WHAT'S NEXT?

04:27.392 --> 04:31.020
{\an1}THE LIMITED EDITION
DARK LASER ACTION FIGURE

04:31.104 --> 04:33.189
FROM THE "SPACE WARS"
COLLECTION.

04:34.857 --> 04:35.984
ONLY 10 INCHES TALL?

04:36.067 --> 04:36.651
FORGET THAT.

04:36.734 --> 04:39.153
I WANT IT TO BE LIFE-SIZE.

04:53.876 --> 04:55.378
AND NOW
I'VE COPIED EVERYTHING

04:55.461 --> 04:56.337
{\an1}FROM THE TOY CATALOG
TO MOM'S COOKBOOK.

04:56.421 --> 05:01.592
{\an1}AND NOW IT'S TIME
TO COPY DAD'S MAGAZINES.

05:12.395 --> 05:16.232
NOW TO TAKE OVER
THIS NEW AND STRANGE WORLD

05:16.315 --> 05:18.609
WITH THESE MIGHTY WEAPONS
OF FIERY DEATH.

05:20.653 --> 05:21.654
HEY! FLIPSIE!

05:23.823 --> 05:25.908
[LAUGHING]

05:25.992 --> 05:27.869
MY VICTORY IS ASSURED.

05:27.952 --> 05:30.955
HA HA HA!

05:31.039 --> 05:32.999
UH,
DR. RIP STUDWELL,

05:33.082 --> 05:34.792
WHAT ABOUT COSMO?

05:37.086 --> 05:38.796
I'M AFRAID HE'S GOT...

05:38.880 --> 05:40.006
DANCER.

05:40.089 --> 05:43.176
NO! WHAT'S THAT?

05:43.259 --> 05:45.636
{\an1}SOMETHING THAT,
IF LEFT UNCHECKED,

05:45.720 --> 05:47.430
{\an1}COULD CAUSE HIM TO GRANT
A STUPID WISH LIKE OH, SAY,

05:47.513 --> 05:50.016
A MAGIC COPIER THAT
COULD POOF UP SOMETHING

05:50.099 --> 05:50.933
THAT MIGHT TRY
TO DESTROY THE WORLD.

05:51.017 --> 05:53.061
OH. YEAH.

05:53.144 --> 05:54.437
THAT WOULD BE STUPID.

05:54.520 --> 05:57.690
THEN I HAVE YOUR
PERMISSION TO ATTEMPT

05:57.774 --> 06:00.359
A RISKY AND INCREDIBLY
PAINFUL OPERATION?

06:03.196 --> 06:04.822
YEP. GOTTA GO. BYE!

06:04.906 --> 06:07.116
GREAT. THEN I...

06:07.200 --> 06:08.034
Cosmo:
DR. RIP STUDWELL...

06:08.117 --> 06:10.453
WILL OPERATE IMMEDIATELY.

06:10.536 --> 06:12.497
AFTER 18 HOLES OF GOLF.

06:15.124 --> 06:16.626
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

06:16.709 --> 06:18.336
Dark Laser:
WEAK PEOPLE OF THIS WORLD,

06:18.419 --> 06:21.130
BOW TO ME, YOUR NEW LEADER,

06:21.214 --> 06:22.590
DARK LASER.

06:22.673 --> 06:26.844
{\an1}SURRENDER, OR FACE FLIPSIE,
THE FLIPPING DOG OF DOOM.

06:26.928 --> 06:27.970
[BARKS]

06:28.054 --> 06:29.806
HEE HEE HEE!

06:29.889 --> 06:31.974
MAN, I NEVER GET TIRED
OF THAT.

06:32.058 --> 06:33.309
THIS IS CHET UBETCHA SAYING,

06:33.392 --> 06:35.103
IT'S DOOMSDAY IN DIMMSDALE!

06:35.186 --> 06:37.772
OR SHALL I SAY DOOMSDALE?

06:37.855 --> 06:41.317
{\an4}I CAN'T WAIT TO COPY
ALL 12 ISSUES OF
"UNDER THE BED MONTHLY."

06:41.400 --> 06:43.486
IN WHAT CAN
ONLY BE DESCRIBED

06:43.569 --> 06:45.071
AS A 10-YEAR-OLD BOY'S
WISH GONE AWRY,

06:45.154 --> 06:47.573
WE'RE ALL DOOMED!

06:47.657 --> 06:48.533
AND IN AN
UNRELATED STORY,

06:48.616 --> 06:49.909
PEOPLE ARE FLIPPING
OVER FLIPSIE.

06:49.992 --> 06:51.911
[BARKS]

06:51.994 --> 06:52.912
HA HA HA!

06:52.995 --> 06:55.039
MAN, I NEVER GET TIRED
OF THAT.

06:55.123 --> 06:57.125
{\an1}OH, SURE.
FLIP FOR THE BAD GUY.

06:57.208 --> 06:58.709
AAH!

07:10.680 --> 07:14.267
{\an5}TIMMY, YOU DIDN'T USE
THE LIFE-SIZE BUTTON,
DID YOU?

07:14.350 --> 07:15.685
UH...

07:17.728 --> 07:19.856
{\an1}I WISH EVERYTHING
WAS BACK TO NORMAL.

07:23.401 --> 07:26.154
WHOA. DIDN'T SEE
THAT COMING.

07:26.237 --> 07:28.656
AAH! WHERE'S COSMO?

07:28.739 --> 07:31.367
{\an1}HE'S STILL AT THE DOCTOR'S,
AND WE'RE OUT OF MAGIC.

07:31.450 --> 07:33.077
{\an1}THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING WE CAN DO.

07:33.161 --> 07:33.870
LIKE WHAT?

07:37.832 --> 07:38.958
MMM!

07:39.041 --> 07:40.126
[GULP]

07:40.209 --> 07:42.712
OK. LET'S ROCK.

07:46.674 --> 07:47.550
I'M COMING WITH YOU.

07:47.633 --> 07:50.803
NO. WITHOUT YOUR WAND,
YOU'RE POWERLESS.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.598
{\an5}YOU'VE GOT TO STAY HERE
AND COPY SOMETHING
IF I NEED IT.

07:53.681 --> 07:56.392
{\an1}JUST BECAUSE I'M A WOMAN
DOESN'T MEAN I'M A SECRETARY.

07:56.475 --> 07:57.894
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

07:57.977 --> 08:00.229
{\an1}TIMMY TURNER'S OFFICE.
PLEASE HOLD.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.231
{\an1}IT'S CHESTER.
ARE YOU IN?

08:08.487 --> 08:10.072
HE'S IN A MEETING.

08:11.616 --> 08:12.700
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

08:31.844 --> 08:35.139
{\an1}WANDA, I NEED YOU TO COPY
MORE POD ROCKETS.

08:35.222 --> 08:37.600
100 MISSILES COMING UP.

08:37.683 --> 08:39.852
AND WOULD IT KILL YOU
TO SAY PLEASE?

08:44.148 --> 08:45.775
[BARKS]

08:45.858 --> 08:50.780
OH, FLIPSIE, YOU AND I WILL RULE
THIS MUD BALL TOGETHER.

08:50.863 --> 08:54.450
YES, WE WILL.
YES, WE WILL, FLIPSIE.

08:54.533 --> 08:55.868
[ALARM]

08:58.871 --> 09:01.874
{\an1}CURSES! FLIPSIE, I'M SORRY
YOU HAD TO HEAR THAT.

09:01.958 --> 09:02.833
NOW TO FIND DARK LASER.

09:05.169 --> 09:07.338
AAH!

09:07.421 --> 09:09.006
[FAST BEEPING]

09:12.551 --> 09:15.221
WANDA, I NEED A NEW ENGINE! NOW!

09:15.304 --> 09:16.055
AND A SODA.
I'M PARCHED.

09:20.268 --> 09:22.186
THE COPIER'S JAMMED!

09:22.270 --> 09:23.604
{\an1}BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS,
I PICKED UP YOUR DRY CLEANING

09:23.688 --> 09:26.232
AND ORGANIZED YOUR PLANNER.

09:27.692 --> 09:31.070
WANDA! DO SOMETHING!

09:31.153 --> 09:33.072
AHEM.

09:33.155 --> 09:34.532
PLEASE.

09:34.615 --> 09:36.826
{\an1}HANG ON, SPORT!
THIS CAN'T BE HARD TO FIX.

09:40.788 --> 09:42.748
HEY, HERE'S THE JAM.

09:44.709 --> 09:47.670
{\an1}AND IT'S BOYSENBERRY.
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

09:47.753 --> 09:48.254
ANYTHING!

09:48.337 --> 09:49.463
YOU GOT IT.

09:49.547 --> 09:52.091
{\an1}AS SOON AS THIS THING
WARMS UP.

09:52.466 --> 09:55.970
AAH! WANDA!

09:59.140 --> 10:01.058
ALMOST THERE.

10:01.642 --> 10:04.020
ONE STAR FIGHTER ENGINE

10:04.103 --> 10:06.314
AND A SODA COMING RIGHT UP.

10:06.397 --> 10:09.525
HEY! HALF A SODA?

10:09.608 --> 10:13.696
HALF AN ENGINE?
WHAT GIVES?

10:13.779 --> 10:15.615
{\an1}BAD NEWS, TIMMY.
WE'RE OUT OF TONER!

10:15.698 --> 10:18.659
AND YOUR 2:00 CANCELED.

10:18.743 --> 10:19.285
AAH!

10:19.368 --> 10:21.203
I'M DOOMED!

10:21.287 --> 10:23.372
I HAVE YOU NOW.

10:23.456 --> 10:26.625
I MEAN, WE HAVE YOU NOW.

10:26.709 --> 10:28.210
HA HA HA HA!

10:31.714 --> 10:33.466
WHEE!

10:33.549 --> 10:35.885
Both: COSMO!

10:35.968 --> 10:38.512
{\an1}THAT'S RIGHT, AND I'M BACK
FROM THE PLUMBER'S.

10:38.596 --> 10:41.974
{\an5}QUICK! I WISH
DARK LASER WAS BACK
IN THE CATALOG.

10:42.058 --> 10:44.226
COPY THAT, GOOD BUDDY!

10:50.691 --> 10:51.359
NOOO!

10:51.442 --> 10:53.652
FLIPSIE!

10:53.736 --> 10:57.114
DON'T FORGET ME!

10:57.198 --> 10:59.909
{\an5}WANDA, LET'S YOU
AND I BOTH AGREE
NOT TO GRANT TIMMY

10:59.992 --> 11:03.746
{\an5}ANY REALLY STUPID
OR DANGEROUS WISHES
EVER AGAIN.

11:03.829 --> 11:05.539
WOW. THAT DR. STUDWELL...

11:05.623 --> 11:07.875
DR. RIP STUDWELL...

11:07.958 --> 11:09.585
SURE CAN OPERATE.

11:09.668 --> 11:10.878
YOU'RE CURED.

11:10.961 --> 11:12.088
OH, HE DIDN'T OPERATE.

11:12.171 --> 11:13.714
THE DANCING
JUST WENT AWAY.

11:13.798 --> 11:16.509
{\an5}LIKE, THERE'S
SOMETHING ELSE IN THERE
OCCUPYING HIS TIME.

11:16.592 --> 11:19.011
[LAUGHS]

11:19.095 --> 11:23.724
{\an1}FLIPSIE, TOGETHER, YOU AND I
WILL TAKE OVER THIS HEAD.

11:23.808 --> 11:28.062
{\an1}WE DID IT!
LET'S CELEBRATE BY DANCING.

11:29.563 --> 11:31.273
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

11:31.357 --> 11:33.943
TIMMY TURNER'S OFFICE.
CAN YOU HOLD?

11:34.026 --> 11:35.986
IT'S DARK LASER.
HE'S ASKING FOR FLIPSIE.

11:36.612 --> 11:39.532
I'M SORRY, HE'S NOT IN.

11:39.615 --> 11:42.243
DON'T GET FLIPPY WITH ME.

11:42.326 --> 11:46.956
{\an1}I'M NEVER GONNA DO
ANYTHING STUPID AGAIN.

11:47.540 --> 11:50.668
AGAIN. AGAIN.

11:50.751 --> 11:54.088
QUIT COPYING ME.
QUIT COPYING ME.

11:54.171 --> 11:55.756
STOP IT! STOP IT!

11:55.840 --> 11:57.967
[FLIPSIE BARKS]

12:12.440 --> 12:13.941
{\an1}DON'T MOVE, OR I'LL FILL YOU
FULL OF LEAD.

12:14.024 --> 12:18.404
{\an5}GIVE US
ALL YOUR SNOW GLOBES,
PEWTER SPOONS,

12:18.487 --> 12:21.073
AND CHOMPIE THE GOAT
SALT AND PEPPER SHAKERS.

12:21.157 --> 12:21.532
NOW, BUNKIE.

12:21.615 --> 12:23.576
THANKS, BUNKIE.

12:23.659 --> 12:26.704
[ROBBERS LAUGHING]

12:26.787 --> 12:29.498
{\an1}Man: MA AND PA TURNBAUM,
A.K.A. THE SOUVENIR BANDITS,

12:29.582 --> 12:30.624
STRIKE AGAIN.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.001
I'M CHET UBETCHA.

12:32.084 --> 12:34.670
{\an1}AND YOU'RE WATCHING
"DIMMSDALE'S MOST WANTED,"

12:34.753 --> 12:36.088
STARRING ME, CHET UBETCHA.

12:36.172 --> 12:38.048
WHOA.

12:38.132 --> 12:38.966
WHOA, INDEED.

12:39.049 --> 12:41.510
{\an1}NOT MUCH IS KNOWN
ABOUT THESE BANDITS,

12:41.594 --> 12:43.345
{\an1}EXCEPT THAT THEY ARE
A MAN AND A WOMAN,

12:43.429 --> 12:44.180
{\an1}SEEM TO BE MARRIED,
LOVE PENCILS,

12:44.263 --> 12:46.849
{\an1}AND ARE TRAVELING
THE COUNTRYSIDE

12:46.932 --> 12:48.559
{\an1}IN A BEAT-UP
RECREATIONAL VEHICLE.

12:48.642 --> 12:49.018
YOU DON'T THINK...

12:49.101 --> 12:51.687
I NEVER THINK.

12:51.770 --> 12:52.646
MY PARENTS
AREN'T CRIMINALS,

12:52.730 --> 12:53.898
AND THEY'RE NOT
THE SOUVENIR BANDITS.

12:53.981 --> 12:57.026
{\an5}WE'RE NOT ON
A CROSS-COUNTRY
CRIME SPREE.

12:57.109 --> 13:00.571
{\an5}WELL, THEN, I GUESS
I WON'T BE NEEDING
THIS FALSE MUSTACHE

13:00.654 --> 13:01.780
{\an5}AND THIS
"CRIMINAL'S GUIDE TO
HIDING IN MEXICO."

13:01.864 --> 13:05.534
{\an5}I JUST HOPE IT
DOESN'T INTERFERE WITH
OUR FAMILY VACATION

13:05.618 --> 13:07.328
TO NIAGARA FALLS.

13:07.411 --> 13:09.705
{\an5}UH, YOU KNOW,
YOU CAN TAKE OFF
YOUR FALSE MUSTACHE.

13:09.788 --> 13:12.458
{\an1}I'M NOT WEARING
A FALSE MUSTACHE.

13:12.541 --> 13:14.335
RIGHT.

13:14.418 --> 13:16.629
LOOK, TIMMY.

13:16.712 --> 13:18.005
DID YOU KNOW
NIAGARA FALLS

13:18.088 --> 13:21.383
IS ONE OF THE 7 NATURAL
WONDERS OF THE WORLD?

13:21.467 --> 13:22.551
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.
RUNNING WATER.

13:22.635 --> 13:24.720
WE HAVE THAT
AT HOME.

13:24.803 --> 13:27.723
{\an1}Dad: IT'S ALSO CONVENIENTLY
LOCATED RIGHT NEXT TO

13:27.806 --> 13:29.725
{\an1}THE NORTH AMERICAN MUSEUM
OF PENCIL PUSHING.

13:29.808 --> 13:31.644
{\an1}AND, AS A PROFESSIONAL
PENCIL PUSHER,

13:31.727 --> 13:32.561
{\an1}IT'S MY DUTY TO
JOURNEY THERE

13:32.645 --> 13:35.731
AND SHARPEN ONE PENCIL

13:35.814 --> 13:38.984
{\an1}IN THE SACRED
SILVER SHARPENER!

13:42.446 --> 13:47.409
[CHEERING]

13:47.493 --> 13:48.744
YAY! WE'RE GOING
TO NIAGARA FALLS,

13:48.827 --> 13:53.457
{\an4}ONE OF THE MOST BEAUTIFUL,
ROMANTIC VACATION SPOTS
IN THE WORLD.

13:53.541 --> 13:54.792
YEAH, AND DESPITE THAT,

13:54.875 --> 13:57.294
I LOVE IT BECAUSE IT'S
PARTIALLY IN CANADA!

13:57.378 --> 13:59.755
I LOVE CANADA!

13:59.838 --> 14:02.383
THEIR TRADITION OF
PEACEFUL COEXISTENCE,

14:02.466 --> 14:05.928
{\an5}THEIR COMMITMENT
TO ENVIRONMENTAL
PROTECTION.

14:06.011 --> 14:07.263
PLUS, THEY'VE GOT A FLAG
WITH A LEAF ON IT!

14:07.346 --> 14:10.057
WOW. A LEAF.

14:10.140 --> 14:12.351
I CAN'T WAIT
TO GET TO CANADA.

14:12.434 --> 14:13.644
OOH! ME NEITHER.

14:13.727 --> 14:15.938
THAT'S WHY WE'RE NOT
STOPPING FOR ANYTHING.

14:16.021 --> 14:18.941
WE'RE STOPPING
FOR SOMETHING!

14:19.024 --> 14:21.610
WAIT! I DON'T HAVE TO GO.

14:21.694 --> 14:22.319
AAH!

14:22.403 --> 14:24.446
[MEN SCREAM]

14:24.530 --> 14:25.864
All: FEMALE!

14:25.948 --> 14:28.659
{\an5}UGH. I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE'VE ONLY TRAVELED
200 MILES.

14:28.742 --> 14:31.954
{\an1}IN CANADA,
THAT'S 320 KILOMETERS.

14:32.037 --> 14:34.039
CAN THIS VACATION
GET ANY WORSE?

14:35.416 --> 14:37.793
WE LOST 'EM, PA.

14:37.876 --> 14:40.588
I TOLD YOU, MA.
NOBODY'S GONNA CATCH...

14:40.671 --> 14:43.382
THE SOUVENIR BANDITS!

14:43.465 --> 14:45.426
[SIRENS]

14:45.509 --> 14:46.719
EXCEPT THEM.

14:46.802 --> 14:50.264
{\an4}I TOLD YOU YOU
SHOULDN'T SHOUT OUR NAMES
IN THE SKY LIKE THAT.

14:51.974 --> 14:55.936
{\an5}QUICK, INTO
THAT EERILY IDENTICAL
MOBILE HOME.

14:56.020 --> 14:59.064
{\an5}IT'S THOSE
HIDEOUS-LOOKING FIENDS
THE TURNBAUMS.

14:59.148 --> 15:02.651
{\an5}GOT TO HIDE IN
THIS BATHROOM MY DAD
WAS TOO STUPID TO USE.

15:04.903 --> 15:07.656
{\an1}MOM AND DAD WILL BE BACK
ANY MINUTE,

15:07.740 --> 15:08.574
{\an1}AND EVERYTHING
WILL BE JUST FINE.

15:08.657 --> 15:12.411
MAN, THAT WAS CLOSE.

15:13.954 --> 15:15.164
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

15:15.247 --> 15:17.833
{\an1}I TOLD YOU NOT TO FOLLOW ME
INTO THE MEN'S ROOM.

15:17.916 --> 15:20.419
{\an1}QUICK, WEAR
THIS FALSE MUSTACHE.

15:20.502 --> 15:22.087
{\an5}GET ON THE HORN
AND TELL THE CHIEF
WE'VE CAPTURED

15:22.171 --> 15:24.673
{\an5}THE SOUVENIR-STEALING
FIENDS THE TURNBAUMS.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.675
{\an1}UH, THAT'S
PRONOUNCED TURNER.

15:26.759 --> 15:27.968
THEY'VE CONFESSED.

15:28.052 --> 15:29.595
WHO'S UP FOR SOME DOUGHNUTS?

15:42.775 --> 15:44.610
I'M WORRIED, HONEY.

15:44.693 --> 15:45.903
WHAT ABOUT TIMMY?

15:45.986 --> 15:47.613
RELAX, SNUGGLEBUTT.

15:47.696 --> 15:50.032
{\an1}HE'S SAFE AND SOUND
IN AN IMPREGNABLE MOTOR HOME.

15:50.115 --> 15:52.534
{\an1}BESIDES, WE'LL BE OUT
IN NO TIME.

15:52.618 --> 15:53.661
{\an4}I'M CONFIDENT THAT
OUR AMERICAN SYSTEM
OF JUSTICE

15:53.744 --> 15:55.204
WILL SEE US THROUGH.

15:58.916 --> 16:00.167
{\an1}UH, THIS MAY TAKE LONGER
THAN I THOUGHT.

16:04.421 --> 16:06.048
{\an1}I'M CHET UBETCHA
WITH BREAKING NEWS.

16:06.131 --> 16:09.593
{\an1}THE NEWLY MUSTACHIOED
SOUVENIR BANDITS

16:09.677 --> 16:11.637
{\an4}HAVE BEEN CAUGHT
AND CONVICTED FOR
A LIFE OF PADDLING.

16:11.720 --> 16:13.931
HOW CONVENIENT.

16:14.014 --> 16:17.518
{\an5}THOSE COPS MISTOOK
THAT HIDEOUS-LOOKING
MARRIED COUPLE FOR US.

16:17.601 --> 16:20.813
WE, THE ACTUAL
TURNBAUMS, ARE FREE!

16:20.896 --> 16:23.232
OOH, I DID IT AGAIN,
DIDN'T I?

16:23.315 --> 16:26.360
{\an1}OH, NO! MY PARENTS
ARE GONNA BE PADDLED!

16:26.443 --> 16:29.113
{\an1}WAIT. CAN'T I JUST
WISH MY PARENTS FREE?

16:29.196 --> 16:31.156
{\an1}THEY'RE ENTWINED
IN THE AMERICAN LEGAL SYSTEM.

16:31.240 --> 16:35.327
{\an4}IT WOULD TAKE YEARS
TO GET THEM OUT,
EVEN WITH MAGIC.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.913
{\an1}WELL, THEN, I HAVE TO SOMEHOW
GET THE TURNBAUMS ARRESTED

16:37.996 --> 16:40.666
{\an1}AND PROVE
MY PARENTS INNOCENT.

16:42.751 --> 16:44.211
I HAVE A PLAN.

16:47.673 --> 16:52.302
{\an5}Pa: "COME SEE THE
NORTH AMERICAN MUSEUM
OF PENCIL PUSHING!"

16:52.386 --> 16:55.139
{\an1}Ma: "HOME OF THE WORLD'S
BEST SOUVENIR:

16:55.222 --> 16:58.058
{\an1}THE SACRED
SILVER SHARPENER."

16:58.142 --> 17:00.394
Pa: "HOME OF
THE WORLD'S WORST

17:00.477 --> 17:02.688
SOUVENIR
SECURITY SYSTEM!"

17:02.771 --> 17:05.273
{\an1}PA, ARE YOU THINKING
WHAT I'M THINKING?

17:05.357 --> 17:08.402
LET'S GO TO CANADA AND
STEAL US A SHARPENER!

17:08.484 --> 17:09.862
DARN IT.

17:09.944 --> 17:11.739
{\an5}AND LET'S GET THERE
BEFORE MY PARENTS
GET CONVICTED.

17:11.821 --> 17:13.991
BUT, TIMMY...

17:14.074 --> 17:15.617
AAH!

17:15.701 --> 17:18.912
{\an5}WE'RE HERE, AND THE
GREATEST COUNTRY ON EARTH
IS WAY OVER THERE.

17:18.996 --> 17:19.913
WE'LL NEVER GET THERE
IN TIME.

17:19.997 --> 17:22.082
YES, WE WILL.

17:22.165 --> 17:24.626
I WISH WE COULD GET TO
NIAGARA FALLS FASTER.

17:40.476 --> 17:42.561
Ma: WOW. WE MADE GREAT TIME.

17:46.356 --> 17:48.192
[MOOSE GRUNTS]

17:48.275 --> 17:49.234
THERE IT IS, MA--

17:49.318 --> 17:51.987
{\an1}THE NORTH AMERICAN MUSEUM
OF PENCIL PUSHING.

17:52.070 --> 17:53.197
SECURITY LOOKS
POWERFUL TIGHT, PA.

17:53.280 --> 17:56.408
{\an1}AAH! I HATE IT WHEN
BILLBOARDS LIE TO ME.

17:56.492 --> 17:58.118
{\an1}NOW WE'LL NEVER
GET INSIDE.

17:58.202 --> 18:00.704
{\an1}LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE
GONNA NEED SOME HELP.

18:02.080 --> 18:04.666
OH, POOH.

18:04.750 --> 18:07.795
I WANTED TO WRITE DOWN
MY HOME PHONE NUMBER.

18:07.878 --> 18:11.089
IF ONLY SOMEBODY HAD A PENCIL
I COULD BORROW...

18:13.091 --> 18:15.135
WHAT LUCK, PA!

18:15.219 --> 18:17.888
WE GOTTA FOLLOW THEM!

18:27.064 --> 18:29.691
{\an1}OOH, THIS IS
GONNA BE A SNAP.

18:33.946 --> 18:36.865
[BOTH GASP]

18:36.949 --> 18:38.492
[BOTH SCREAM]

18:41.245 --> 18:44.039
OH, NO! THEY'RE GONNA
GET SQUASHED!

18:44.122 --> 18:44.873
I WISH THERE WAS
A SECOND HALLWAY.

18:44.957 --> 18:47.459
YOU GOT IT.

18:49.503 --> 18:51.922
{\an1}HEY, LET'S GO DOWN
THIS SECOND HALLWAY.

18:55.467 --> 18:57.386
THERE'S NO WAY
TO OPEN THIS DOOR.

18:57.469 --> 18:59.263
{\an1}AAH! THE ONLY WAY
TO GET IN IS TO SOLVE

18:59.346 --> 19:03.058
{\an7}THE RIDDLE OF THE SACRED
SILVER SHARPENER...

19:07.688 --> 19:09.147
UH, MOTOR OIL.

19:09.231 --> 19:11.149
CRAB CAKES?

19:09.231 --> 19:11.149
GREEN BEANS?

19:11.233 --> 19:12.651
WHAT? HOW STUPID
ARE THESE PEOPLE?

19:12.734 --> 19:15.654
MAPLE SYRUP, CANADA'S
NUMBER ONE EXPORT?

19:15.737 --> 19:16.989
OH, FOR THE LOVE OF...

19:17.072 --> 19:18.740
ERASER!

19:21.368 --> 19:23.745
HEY! IT WAS
CRAB CAKES!

19:42.598 --> 19:44.182
AH, THE HECK WITH IT.

19:44.266 --> 19:47.477
[ALARM]

19:52.274 --> 19:54.359
[SCREAMING]

19:56.945 --> 19:58.572
I WISH WE WERE OUT OF HERE.

20:00.908 --> 20:04.328
{\an4}AWESOME! NOW ALL
WE HAVE TO DO IS WAIT
FOR THE CANADIAN COPS.

20:04.411 --> 20:06.872
OR, AS THEY'RE CALLED
IN CANADA, MOUNTIES!

20:06.955 --> 20:09.166
{\an1}TO NAIL THE TURNBAUMS
AND SET MY PARENTS FREE.

20:09.249 --> 20:12.377
UH, TIMMY...

20:12.461 --> 20:13.295
NO ONE WILL
EVER CATCH US,

20:13.378 --> 20:16.131
THE REAL
SOUVENIR BANDITS,

20:16.214 --> 20:21.553
{\an5}FROM ESCAPING
OVER THE FALLS
IN THIS RUBBER RAFT!

20:21.637 --> 20:23.138
WHICH WE STOLE.

20:23.221 --> 20:25.349
{\an1}WHAT? BUT WHERE
ARE THE COPS?

20:25.432 --> 20:27.559
{\an5}USE MY PENCIL.

20:25.432 --> 20:27.559
TAKE MY PENCIL.

20:27.643 --> 20:28.560
COME ON.

20:28.644 --> 20:30.312
WE CAN'T LET THEM ESCAPE.

20:31.647 --> 20:34.232
I WISH YOU GUYS WERE
A SUPER FAST SPEEDBOAT.

20:51.458 --> 20:54.169
PICK IT UP, COSMO.

20:54.252 --> 20:56.880
SORRY, TIMMY, BUT THE WATER
SPEED LIMIT IN CANADA IS--

20:56.964 --> 20:58.423
AAH!

20:58.507 --> 21:00.342
THEY'RE GETTING AWAY.

21:00.425 --> 21:03.345
WE'RE GETTING AWAY!

21:03.428 --> 21:05.305
WANDA, I WISH I HAD A PENCIL.

21:07.766 --> 21:11.853
I HOPE I INHERITED
SOME PENCIL PROWESS FROM MY DAD.

21:17.442 --> 21:18.694
WE CAUGHT 'EM.

21:18.777 --> 21:21.279
{\an1}WE CAUGHT
THE SOUVENIR BANDITS.

21:21.363 --> 21:23.699
{\an5}OOH, SOMEBODY SHOULD
CALL THE AMERICANS
AND TELL THEM

21:23.782 --> 21:26.201
TO FREE THOSE TWO
OTHER GUYS, EH?

21:26.284 --> 21:29.204
{\an1}COOL. NOW THEY HAVE
TO SET MY PARENTS FREE.

21:29.288 --> 21:32.541
{\an5}WHAT? I COULDN'T
HEAR YOU OVER THE
ROAR OF THE FALLS.

21:32.624 --> 21:34.418
All: FALLS?!

21:34.501 --> 21:37.963
[SCREAMING]

21:40.549 --> 21:43.010
I WISH I COULD FLY!

21:45.470 --> 21:48.056
{\an1}SEE? I MADE HIM A LOON,
THE NATIONAL BIRD OF CANADA.

21:48.140 --> 21:52.060
{\an4}AND I MADE US DODOS,
THE EXTINCT FLIGHTLESS
BIRD OF CANADA.

21:52.144 --> 21:56.148
YOU IDIOT! DO SOMETHING!

21:59.484 --> 22:02.612
COSMO!

22:03.155 --> 22:05.323
Man: TIMMY TURNER,

22:05.407 --> 22:08.201
{\an5}FOR BRAVERY ABOVE
AND BEYOND THE CALL
OF AN AMERICAN CHILD,

22:08.285 --> 22:12.289
{\an5}WE PRESENT TO YOU
OUR HIGHEST
PENCIL-BASED HONOR--

22:12.372 --> 22:14.041
THE BRONZE PENCIL.

22:16.084 --> 22:19.004
{\an5}AND FOR THE
MIDDLE-MANAGING
PENCIL PUSHER

22:19.087 --> 22:21.590
WHO BROUGHT THIS
CHILD TO US,

22:21.673 --> 22:23.508
IT IS TIME.

22:26.136 --> 22:27.721
OOH! AT LAST.

22:27.804 --> 22:30.682
MY LIFELONG DREAM
REALIZED.

22:30.766 --> 22:32.267
OTHER THAN BEING MARRIED
TO YOU, HONEY.

22:48.492 --> 22:50.452
[CROWD GASPS]

22:52.162 --> 22:53.080
[GASPS]

22:53.163 --> 22:55.040
NOW, NOW, DARLING,
SNUGGLEBUTT,

22:55.123 --> 22:56.666
DON'T WORRY. IT WAS
JUST AN ACCIDENT.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.293
BESIDES,
I'M CONFIDENT

22:58.376 --> 23:00.629
{\an5}THE CANADIAN
JUSTICE SYSTEM
WILL SEE US THROUGH.

23:03.840 --> 23:05.967
{\an1}UH, THIS MIGHT TAKE LONGER
THAN I THOUGHT.

23:06.051 --> 23:06.635
BUT IN CANADIAN TIME,
THAT'S--

23:06.718 --> 23:08.136
Pa: QUIET OVER THERE!

23:08.220 --> 23:11.973
{\an1}WE, THE REAL TURNBAUMS,
ARE BEING PADDLED!

23:12.057 --> 23:14.643
Ma: STOP THAT!

23:14.726 --> 23:15.560
Pa: DARN IT!

